   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Hello paulproteus,

I had read about this bug, I tried FireBug/Chrome DOM inspector to change the 
CSS of the code and as per your bug specification found 'code' elements/tags are 
working fine outside the class named 'raquo_bullets'. So there some change in 
needed to apply the code tags written under 'li' elements/tags. There are more 
pages suffering from this issue.

other pages are

<a href="http://openhatch.org/missions/diffpatch/recursive_diff">http://openhatch.org/missions/diffpatch/recursive_diff</a>
<a href="http://openhatch.org/missions/svn/diff">http://openhatch.org/missions/svn/diff</a>
<a href="http://openhatch.org/missions/svn/commit">http://openhatch.org/missions/svn/commit</a>

I have changed the CSS in base.less
ul.raquo_bullets {
    ....
    li{
        ....
        code {
            ....
        }
    }
}</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
